### USAGE: .achievement add <achievement>
Add an achievement, specified by ID or link, to the targeted player.

### USAGE: .account set addon [<accountname>] <expansion>
Sets the specified account's, or targeted player's account's expansion level. 0 = WoW, 1 = TBC, 2 = WotLK.

### USAGE: .account set sec regmail <accountname> <email> <confirm email>
Replaces the registration email on record for the specified account.

### USAGE: .account set sec email <accountname> <email> <confirm email>
Replaces the email on record for the specified account.

### USAGE: .account set 2fa <accountname> <secret>
Provide a base32 encoded secret to setup two-factor authentication for the account.
Specify 'off' to disable two-factor authentication for the account.

### USAGE: .account set seclevel [<accountname>] <level> [<realm>]
Set the security level for the specified account, or the targeted player's account, to the specified level on the specified realm.
Cannot be used on self. Levels range from 0 (player) to 3 (administrator). Realm ID defaults to -1 (all realms).

### USAGE: .account set password <accountname> <password> <confirm password>
Changes the password for the specified account.

### USAGE: .account 2fa setup
Begins setup of two-factor authentication for this account.

### USAGE: .account 2fa remove <token>
Provide a current 2FA token to disable two-factor authentication for this account.

### USAGE: .account addon <expansion>
Sets this account's expansion level. 0 = WoW, 1 = TBC, 2 = WotLK.

### USAGE: .account create <name> <password> [<email>]
Creates a new account with the specified password and email (if specified).

### USAGE: .account delete <name>
Deletes the specified account. Cannot be used on self while connected.

### USAGE: .account email <old email> <password> <new email> <confirm new email>
Changes the email on record for this account.

### USAGE: .account onlinelist
Shows a list of all currently-connected accounts.

### USAGE: .account lock country <on/off>
While enabled, you will only be able to log in from IP addresses in your current country.

### USAGE: .account lock ip <on/off>
While enabled, you will only be able to log in from your current IP address.

### USAGE: .account password <old password> <new password> <confirm password> [<email>]
Changes the password for this account.
Whether you need to specify your email address depends on the server settings.

### USAGE: .account
Prints information about the current account.

### USAGE: .learn <spell> [all]
Teaches the specified spell.
If 'all' is specified, teaches all ranks of the spell instead.

### USAGE: .unlearn <spell> [all]
Removes the specified spell from the target's spellbook.
If 'all' is specified, removes all ranks of the spell instead.

### USAGE: .learn my quests
Teaches you any spells your class can obtain through class quests.

### USAGE: .learn my trainer
Teaches you any spells you could currently train at your class trainer.

### USAGE: .learn all blizzard
Teaches you all available Blizzard internal spells.

### USAGE: .learn all debug
Teaches you a set of spells useful for testing raid encounters.
You shouldn't be using GM commands during testing - they can cause weird behavior on their own!

### USAGE: .learn all crafts [<player>]
Teaches the specified player, or target/self, all available professions and recipes

### USAGE: .learn all default [<player>]
Teaches the specified player, or target/self, all default spells for their race/class, as well as any quests they have unlocked through quests.

### USAGE: .learn all languages
Teaches all available languages.

### USAGE: .learn all recipes <profession>
Teaches all recipes for the given profession.

### USAGE: .learn all talents
Unlocks all talents for the player's class.

### USAGE: .learn all pettalents
Unlocks all talents for the player's pet.
